3.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Kiting and Exping Galore</span><hr size=1> Ok here it is. Im going to ding 52 soon and will post my little list of where to go at what level =)<br>
<br>
level 1-10 I spent soloing in qeynos and surrounding areas.<br>
1gold or more / 45min<br>
<br>
level 10-16 Group in NRO<br>
1gold or more / 45min<br>
<br>
level 16-22 Group at Mud Pit in OT<br>
1gold or more / 50min<br>
<br>
level 22-29 Soloing in Stonebrunt Mountains killing Kobolds<br>
1gold or more / hour<br>
<br>
level 30-35 Grouping in OT at the &quot;ledge&quot;<br>
1gold or more / 50min (1gold in 40 mins with good group)<br>
<br>
level 36-42 Quad Kiting Dire Wolves in IC<br>
1gold or more /50min (record 1 gold in less than 40min)<br>
<br>
level 42-48 Quad Kiting Dwarves in BB. (Great loot) Make sure you get the ones on right faction. Ask any high level druid or quad wiz in the zone about it and they will know which ones.<br>
1gold or more / 50min<br>
<br>
level 49-50 Quad Kiting Spirocs in TD.<br>
1gold or more / 75min<br>
<br>
level 51-current Quad kiting Wyverns in CS (Great loot!)<br>
With items giving me 270 mana and int at 200 I have about<br>
1 blue mana bub to spare after each quad.<br>
Make sure you check which gems you can sell to vendors<br>
and which to sell in EC for 3-500pp<br>
1gold or more / 150min (Hell)<br>
<br>
current-60  Hope to see more quad kiting areas in SoL<br>
But if there are none, I will go for wyverns untill I ding 56<br>
and then I will AE group.<br>
<br>
How to Quad:<br>
<br>
First of all you must do two quests.<br>
The most important one is JBoots (Instant SOW).<br>
The second is Staff of Temperate flux (Pull and lower res).<br>
Once you have these items you are all set to kite your way <br>
through the levels. It's always fun to have people exclaim<br>
&quot;Wow, you sure have levelled fast &quot;your nick&quot; since we met&quot;<br>
<br>
The quad itself consists of four basic rules.<br>
<br>
-Setup, i.e. which spells to mem and some other things to do.<br>
You can choose what you like yourself.<br>
I use one AoE nuke (lvl 34 CoF and later lvl 51 PoF),<br>
one AoE snare (BoF)<br>
one root (root)<br>
one small DD nuke (fast cast time)<br>
one mid dmg DD nuke (fast cast time)<br>
one shield (the best at your current level)<br>
Harvest (great for getting mana for finish or less downtime)<br>
Gate (sometimes things dont turn out the way you wish).<br>
ALWAYS make sure you have full mana before pulling.<br>
You never know when that last half bub of mana would have saved you from dying by casting snare/root-gate.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Know the surrounding area, i.e. you should always check for<br>
open spaces (see next point), which mobs to kite, and if there are any other players that needs to be taken in consideration so you dont train them.<br>
<br>
-The pull, i.e. You zap four mobs with staff of temp. flux in a way that makes it certain that they will not make other mobs aggro you or that they will get near enough to hurt you.<br>
When you have four mobs running after you, you go to that open area I was talking about and here you do one lap in a large circle, which will ensure you that the mobs are now bustled together.  Then you run away from the mobs while zapping one of them with staff of temp. flux tuntill it says <br>
&quot;target out of range&quot;  Once you do that you stop, turn around, and cast Bonds of Force. Hopefully you will now have four snared mobs after you and can procede to the next point.<br>
If any mob resist BoF you just make sure you snare that one too, and then bundle all four togeteher again and cast BoF untill all four are snared _simultaneously_ (important).<br>
You may now proceed to the next point.<br>
<br>
-The Finish, i.e. Once all four mobs are snared you just kite them by zapping and running away from them untill out of range and the turning around and nuking (the fun part =).<br>
Some mobs will have enough hp that you will be required to resnare them after about 90sec or so. Always make sure<br>
you dont forget to resnare. If one mob resists a bit too much<br>
and are still standing when the others are dead, you can finish it with some mana efficient single target DD nuke. <br>
If out of mana just cast root, or get some ground between you and the mob and then cast Harvest (will stun you but its a great way to wrench out that last mana needed to finish a  resisting mob) <br>
After 1,5 to 3 minutes of nuking you should<br>
now be one happy camper, having gained more exp/time<br>
than any other class may do (except druids).<br>
<br>
Ok this is all I have to say about that. =)<br>
<br>
Feel free to flame me or post faults in my plan hehe.  <br>
