</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 11/15/01 8:50:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzordok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zordok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/15/01 10:10:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Kiting and Exping Galore</span><hr size=1> Actually, when I was grouped in OT from level 28-34, I was consistantly getting 1yellow per hour in any decent group.  The really good pulling groups (usually with both a bard and chanter present) I was pulling down almost one and a half yellows per hour.  So, yeah, it's pretty comparable to quadding at that level. <br>
<br>
However, your point about time spent lfg is true enough.  The key is to zone in at a crucial time when lots of other people are logging on -- I noticed lots of lfg shouts around 5:30pm est during the week, at the conclusion of football games on Sundays and after some of the more popular TV shows ended (ER, West Wing etc).  You might not get picked up by other groups, but it was usually pretty easy to have all the lfgs meet at the ledge and start a new group.  Just takes a little initiative on your part to get things going.  It got me a pretty decent rep in the zone while I levelled there.  <br>
<br>
Of course, now I've spent the last 5 levels quadding ulthorks in EW (thanks Bic!) since I finally got my Jboots.  So, that rep has probably disappeared in the last month or so of solitude.<br>
<br>
Zordok Krenzenkull<br>
44 Wizard<br>
E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucaelestor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caelestor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/01 10:57:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Kiting and Exping Galore</span><hr size=1> The time spent looking for a group in OT are worth it..<br>
